<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="8" pageNumber="584" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1643,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1751,1778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="584">Description.</emphasis>
Length 4.5–5.0 mm. Head, pronotum, sutural line, base of elytra and antennal segments 3–11 reddish brown; antennal segments 1–2, palpi and legs reddish yellow; elytra brownish black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1643,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="584">Head stout, as long as wide, smooth, glabrous; frontal foveae clear, moderately deep; eyes protruding; antennae short, stout, not reaching the middle of the elytra, antennal apical segment longest, segment 3 shorter than segment 1 and 2 combined.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1643,2030]" pageId="8" pageNumber="584">Pronotum as wide as long, punctated, pubescent; disc with apical and basal margins straight, lateral portion of apical margin slightly projecting forward; disc laterally with anterior 2/3rd convex, posterior 1/3rd divergent, hind angle blunt, obtuse, projecting laterally; median groove faint, superficial; lateral bead very narrow, dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="585">Elytra convex, base narrow, humerus straight, corners rounded, narrow, pubescent with closely placed setae; apex with a very faint re-entrant angle, having a membranous border; scutellum very small; lateral margin of disc lined with a flat, reddish yellow bead which increases in width towards apex; very weak striations; sutural colour extending to the apex, broadest at base, extending between first and third striae, gradually narrowed towards apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
